Learning Flash Photography with Grid! 

"Flash photography sirf light add karne ka tareeka nahi, balki ek creative tool hai jo aapki photos ko cinematic bana sakta hai! ⚡✨ Aaj ke shoot me maine flash aur grid modifier ka use kiya hai taake light ko control karke ek dramatic effect create kiya ja sake. Grid light ko spread hone se rokti hai aur ek directional effect deti hai, jo subject ko alag se highlight karta hai. 

 Tips for Beginners:
✅ Grid ka use – Light sirf subject pe focus hoti hai, background dark ho sakta hai.
✅ Shutter Speed Control – High-speed sync (HSS) se daylight me bhi flash use kar sakte ho.
✅ Soft Light vs. Hard Light – Grid softbox ya bare flash ke sath kaise effect deta hai, usko compare karo.
✅ Experiment with Angles – Flash ki direction change karke alag-alag looks try karo.

I credit this with being the #1 thing that took my wedding photography business from 5 weddings one year to 25 weddings the next year…

…which truly allowed me to go full time as a photographer in 2009.

This is an email list, where you can collect email addresses from guests at weddings and send them the gallery of images from the couple.

NOW TWO THINGS…

Clear this with the couple first and make sure they’re ok with it, but it is truly a service for them because then they don’t have to share the gallery with their guests
Do not spam these people, people are reluctant to give up their email addresses and you are responsible to use them wisely.

What I would do after the wedding is put up a blog post within 1 week of the wedding while the energy and excitement is still there, and send it to the email list and let them know that I’ll be sending the full gallery within 8-12 weeks (you can insert whatever your turn around time is, I had the slowest turn around time of anyone I knew )

If you do all of this, the marketing power here is tremendous, and things like this are why I always say the hardest thing is getting your first five clients, find those and you can turn it into a full time business.

If you’re a photographer who could use some support in your business and with your craft, I’m launching a group called inspired and profitable on July 1st. Initially I’m opening it to 25 people, fill out the application in my bio if you’re interested.

caption:
5 Tips for Photographing the Dinner at a Wedding

1️⃣ Capture the Details First: Arrive early to photograph the untouched tables—focus on centerpieces, place cards, table settings, and any unique decor. These shots help tell the story of the couple’s vision for their day.

2️⃣ Use Soft, Natural Light: Dinner lighting can be tricky, often dim and warm. Use a fast lens to make the most of available light, and bring a discreet flash or continuous light for balance without overpowering the ambiance.

3️⃣ Candid Guest Reactions Are Gold: Keep an eye out for genuine moments—laughter, clinking glasses, or heartwarming interactions during speeches and toasts. These authentic emotions make for unforgettable photos.

4️⃣ Capture the Couple’s Perspective: Photograph the couple enjoying their meal, watching speeches, or reacting to their guests. These moments reflect their connection to the event and their loved ones.

5️⃣ Document the Atmosphere: Go beyond individual shots—capture wide shots of the entire room to showcase the ambiance, and include interactions between guests to highlight the warmth and joy of the evening.

The dinner is a special part of the wedding day filled with love, laughter, and connection—don’t miss the chance to capture its magic! ✨️

caption: Sometimes a moment calls for a documentary approach - the ability to capture mood and emotion “on the fly” with looseness and grit, and other times nothing but grace and delicious detail will do. In this image, Xiao’s phenomenal gown is taking center stage as the main story piece so nothing would do but intricate layers of retouching in order to bring out all the details in the beadwork while allowing the surrounding landscape to feel realistically captured. Obtaining high quality post production techniques can take years of formal training. Knowing how much to retouch, and on which images to double down, as well as when enough is enough is all about knowing the context and developing your signature style.  My training began in 2007 at The University of Plymouth (UK), with extensive color and black and white darkroom modules, combined with several semesters on translating the same skills to digital software. There’s always a level deeper to take the edit ... but knowing when to stop is just as important.

PHOTOGRAPHY WORKSHOP 2.0. | Bookings are open now 

The second edition of our photography workshop takes place on November 9-10 in Berlin. The ticket sale has started today! To buy a ticket, please fill in the form via the link in my profile.

The workshop will be held over two days and focus on bridal, wedding and couple photography. It will consist of a theoretical part and a Q&A session with me as well as of three styled shoots that we poor our whole hearts into!

So looking forward to meeting the new attendees and creating together! 

If you have any questions - always - just write me! 

See some of you very soon!

2 years ago during a drive back from Mount Rainier, @rainandpines and I nervously discussed about hosting our own photography workshop

The one question that I asked us over and over again before launching anything was “Why us? Why @heydarlingworkshop ? What do we have to offer?” We don’t have much. All we have is our hearts, our authenticity, and our passion to inspire from within.

3 days with 15 attendees and 18 staff members in the island of Kauai, I was and am still amazed and speechless of every single person who not only showed up but showed up with intentionality. 
We provided some killer contents but our workshop was so much more than epic landscapes and breathtaking photos. We faced crazy weather together. We broke down walls we built from life. We shared our vulnerabilities. We bared our hearts to one another. We inspired from within. We grew together.

To all my darlings, thank you. When you left, you left a piece of your heart in mine. Until next time :) Last but not least, today is the official launch of the next Hey Darling and we are already sold out during presale. From the bottom of my heart, thank you

Our popular 3 Day Wedding Workshop is selling fast for this March.

Link in bio to book your spot.

This 3 Day workshop is a blend hands-on shooting, classroom theory, editing techniques and business tips t get your photography thriving. The time spent in the classroom is focussed on theory such as how to approach the wedding day, the best equipment to use, different shooting styles, selling wedding albums and framing, marketing yourself and what todays clients want.

You will take part in two excellent half-day shoots with several professional bride and groom models at various locations.

Photo credit @benjamintomsphotography 

“I’d highly recommend the three day wedding workshop! I did it a few weeks ago and couldn’t ask for a better group and the tutors had so much knowledge and advice they passed on! I came away from it and dived right in and now have my first wedding shoot booked within two weeks. You won’t regret it!” #weddingphotographytraining #weddingphotographertraining #weddingphotographyworkshop #weddingphotographerworkshop #weddingphotographybusiness #weddingphotographereducation

With everything that I do, I focus a lot on “Intentionality” and “Experience”. My darlings at @heydarlingworkshop know this about me.

Those two characteristics compliment one another. Not just in education but also in photographing couples and most importantly in LIFE.

Hey Darling is not just another workshop. It’s an experience of letting go so we can taking in once again the rediscovery of who we are, why we do what we do, and how to keep that fire burning in the long run.

To all my darlings, you came to the workshop to learn but when you left, you also left a piece of you in little corners of my heart. We are now one big darling family.

Life is harder now than ever and the next few months will be tough, I’ll be there and will always be there for you. Don’t go through life alone!

Hosting Fearless Fireflies at Chaucer Barn means not only capturing stunning images but also immersing ourselves in an atmosphere that fuels creativity. Whether it’s the dreamy outdoor spaces or the character-filled interiors, every corner of this venue is a photographer’s dream.

We can’t wait to welcome our attendees to this incredible space on May 20, 2025! If you’re ready to elevate your wedding photography, push creative boundaries, and capture jaw-dropping editorial content, this is the workshop for you.

Stay tuned for more details—and if you’re as excited as we are, drop a ✨ in the comments!

RAPID FIRE: Questions to ask before booking your wedding photographer 

Choosing someone to preserve your wedding day is a BIG deal. These are the photos and videos you’ll look back on for years to come—maybe even pass down to future generations. So, how do you make sure you’re finding the perfect match? Ask all the right questions!

General Media Q's:
✨ Do you specialize in weddings?
✨ How would you describe your shooting & editing style?
✨ Can I see full galleries or wedding films from weddings that were similar to mine?
✨ Have you worked at my venue or a similar setting?
✨ Do your packages include any planning services?
✨ What type of equipment do you use, do you have backup equipment?
✨ How will you be backing up our photos and videos?
✨ Will we be able to work with you to create a shotlist for our wedding day?
✨ Do you provide sneak peeks, and when?
✨ How long is your editing process?
✨ What’s included in your final deliverables?

For photographers specifically:
 How many photos can I expect in my final gallery?
 Will my gallery include black and white photos?
 Are digital downloads and printing rights included in your photography packages?
 Do you offer prints or album design?

Hiring the right photographer/videographer means more than just loving their work...it’s about making sure they align with your vision, needs, and expectations. So, don’t be afraid to ask these questions!

If you need help finding a photographer who’s the perfect fit, get in touch! Let’s discuss each of these questions to make sure your wedding day is in good hands.

The magic of film ✨

There’s something so special about shooting on film—the depth, the softness, the way it captures light in the most nostalgic way. But let’s be real… exposing it properly is an art in itself! Too much light, and you risk losing detail. Too little, and you get that moody underexposed look (which, don’t get me wrong, has its own charm too ). Every frame is a lesson in patience, precision, and pure creative joy. ️

If you love the timeless, romantic feel of film photography, imagine your wedding day captured this way—every moment preserved with that dreamy, nostalgic touch. Let’s create something beautiful together. ✨

Now booking 2026 weddings & 2025 with limited availability—DM to start planning your dream day!

How to Guarantee Your Wedding Photos Feel Natural (Even If You Hate Posing)”
ㅤ
Let’s face it: Most couples dread wedding photos.
ㅤ
Not because they dislike memories—but because they fear looking awkward or forced.
ㅤ
The problem?
ㅤ
Traditional posing creates tension. When you’re told to “smile naturally” or “hold that pose,” it’s nearly impossible to relax.
ㅤ
The solution I use for UK couples (Birmingham to Brighton):
ㅤ
⬇️ 3 Proven Techniques to capture authentic moments without rigid posing:
ㅤ
1️⃣ The “Distraction Method”
ㅤ
Instead of directing poses, I ask couples to whisper a secret or recall their first date.
ㅤ
Result: Genuine laughter, not stiff smiles.
ㅤ
2️⃣ Silent Storytelling
ㅤ
Focus on unstructured moments (e.g., fixing a tie, adjusting the veil).
ㅤ
Why it works: Candid shots capture raw emotion, which resonates most with couples.
ㅤ
3️⃣ Location-Specific Expertise
ㅤ
I adapt techniques to venues across the UK—castles, barns, urban spaces—to highlight your unique story.
ㅤ
Example: Softening harsh manor-house lighting to emphasize spontaneous joy.
ㅤ
Why share this?
ㅤ
Because 72% of couples prioritize “natural-looking photos” but struggle to articulate their vision (2025 Wedding Trends Report).
ㅤ
Thoughts? What’s your biggest challenge with wedding photos?
ㅤ

Kima Tulum is where romance feels electric, cradled by the pulse of a jungle that’s alive with cicada songs and the whisper of palm fronds swaying like old hymns. It’s the kind of place where love runs barefoot, where the air tastes like salt and tequila, and the sunsets bleed tangerine and rose into the Caribbean. Here, passion isn’t dressed up—it’s raw, untamed, like vows spoken under the open sky with only the moon as your witness. The tables are set simply but beautifully, draped in linen and scattered with candles that flicker like fireflies, their glow mingling with the stars above. Kima doesn’t ask you to perform; it simply begs you to be—wild, free, and hopelessly in love.

Nie mogę się doczekać, by znów stanąć razem z Wami, obok aparatów, w urokliwych plenerach, gdzie światło tańczy jak szalone. Pierwsza edycja tych warsztatów – „Weekendy z mistrzami: Kroniki miłosne” – była jak piorun emocji i twórczości, który zostawił mnie z poczuciem, że to jest właśnie to. Chcę, żebyście przeżyli to samo – zrozumieli intymność, uchwycili te chwile, które mówią więcej niż słowa, i stworzyli kadry, które zostają w pamięci na zawsze. To nie tylko nauka, to podróż – pełna emocji, autentyczności i piękna. Wskakujcie do tego kreatywnego wiru ze mną, obiecuję, będziecie chcieli więcej.

\\I can’t wait to be there with you again – cameras ready, in those charming settings where the light dances wild. The first edition of these workshops – „Weekends with Masters: Chronicles of Love” – hit me like a bolt of emotion and creativity, leaving me knowing this is it. I want you to feel that too – to understand intimacy, capture those moments that speak louder than words, and create frames that last a lifetime. This isn’t just a workshop; it’s a ride – packed with emotion, authenticity, and beauty. Jump into this creative whirlwind with me, and trust me, you’ll crave for more.

Have you ever had this experience?⁠ ⁠
⁠
You complete a shoot. You have clear favorites and images you consider to be “winners” and, while you’re happy with everything you created, your client loves completely different images than you do. Sometimes, you’re left scratching your head thinking, “Why don’t they see what I see?”...⁠
⁠
But, isn’t that how it always goes?⁠
⁠
It’s the same in the art world too.⁠
⁠
Whether it’s a wedding you just delivered or a collection of images for wall art, people are drawn to different images for a myriad of reasons. Some are attracted to the lighting or color, while others love an image for the emotions it makes them feel or because it unlocks a certain memory, still others take a logical approach and find their favorites lie in images that match their decor.⁠
⁠
Art, much like life, is a kaleidoscope of perspectives. Embrace the diverse ways your work resonates with others, and remember, every image has it’s own story to tell. Keep creating, and let your lens capture the magic that speaks to hearts in ways only your art can. ✨ ⁠
.⁠

Your 5 wedding day posing tips! ⤵️

1️⃣ Whatever is closest to the camera looks proportionally larger. To minimize your tummy and hips, lean forward at the waist, emphasizing your bust and face. Keep your chin down so your eyes are closest to the camera.

2️⃣ To create an hourglass shape, turn your body side on to the camera and place your weight on the back leg. Then with your toe on the ground, bring up the front leg by bending the knee.

3️⃣ Hold your bouquet much lower than you think. You don’t want the bouquet to cover your chest or dress. You should hold it at your navel or even crotch level.

4️⃣ Create space between your arms and body to define your waist. Avoid pressing your arms in. Instead, create a small, natural gap by slightly bending your elbows and holding them just away from your body. Not too much as a 90 degree angle appears masculine.

5️⃣ Engage your core for better posture. Slightly tighten your stomach muscles as though you're pulling your belly button in towards your spine. This elongates your torso and projects confidence.

➡️ These tips are about projecting confidence and looking good on camera.

Though sometimes it’s about creating a flattering figure, we understand not everyone’s goal is to appear slimmer. Ultimately if you feel confident, you’ll feel GOOD and not AWKWARD. That's what we want for you on your wedding day!

And don't worry! You won't be able to keep all these tips in mind at all times.   It's nice to have this in your back pocket in case you feel at a loss. Your photographer will guide you!

Follow along - tons more wedding posing tips to come!

caption:
Brodie & Ben 

From our very first chat, I knew Brodie & Ben’s wedding was going to be the vibe. Set in the beautiful Yea countryside, surrounded by rolling hills and endless views, with plenty of friends, family, and all three dogs adding to the celebration, it was always going to be an incredible day.

These two kept things elegant yet fun and relaxed, with loads of personal touches, like Brodie repurposing her mum’s wedding dress, and Ben ensuring there was a steady supply of Gatorade at reception to match his Ironman attitude (I can also personally confirm, this was a great choice on a country summer's day ). Not to mention the glamping on-site for all partygoers, the stunning gum tree shaded ceremony location, and Brodie’s early reception dress change because, why not? It looked too good for their sunset photos. ☀️

I could go on and on but for now, I’ll let the photos do the talking. Congrats again Brodie & Ben!

caption:
“I’m so glad my wedding photographer did documentary style, he captured it like the chaotic day it was. It looks like a war zone. And during the portraits, he really captured a true representation of how uncomfortable I was in front of a camera. Then us eating later in the night... my fav!”. 

Said NO clients ever!

So maybe we do love documentary wedding photography. But maybe it’s doesn’t have to be true, 100% documentary and maybe we can create a different story and a better experience through photography?

The trick is to make your couples feel like you are a “documentary wedding photographer”, but you actually make them feel comfortable when they need it, you have the confidence to direct if they need it and you step in and help when they need it ❤️

On monday I am hosting a FREE live workshop on styled shoots and I’ll be talking all about how to become a director so you can take control without anyone even noticing! Interested? Why wouldn’t ya be?! It’s bloody free and value packed.

Wow, has it been hot!

While you may have air conditioning while getting ready and during transport, what about your ceremony? Your guests will likely arrive 30 minutes early, standing in the sun or seeking shade.

Here are a few simple ways to keep you and your guests comfortable on your special day:

 Hydration Station – Providing water ensures everyone stays refreshed.
 Hand Fans – A thoughtful touch that adds both elegance and practicality.
 Shade Solutions – If your ceremony location lacks natural shade, consider stylish covers to maintain a beautiful aesthetic for your photos.
 Fly Protection – Warm weather invites unwanted guests; adding insect repellent to your essentials can make all the difference.

A little preparation goes a long way in ensuring a comfortable and enjoyable day for everyone.

Hey it’s me; Sunny. 

I think I am supposed to insert something engaging and clever about being a wedding and christening photographer in Perth but I think we need to talk about something far more important. 

Has anyone watched the Netflix series One Day?
If you answered “yes” to that, did you sob to the point of ugly crying? I think I’m going to cry about it AGAIN just thinking about the end.

The next morning I messaged my husband and told him how much I loved him and how I remember how soft his shirt felt against my arm when I first sat next to him 18 years ago.  He told me he loved me too and that the local butcher was having an insane special on Wagyu brisket and we needed some. 

As funny as that may seem, it feels inexplicably precious to have had that exchange after watching One Day. Later that day, something I’d forgotten about resurfaced in what now seems rather serendipitous. My daughter came home from school and wanted a pair of heels to play dress up with. I try to avoid heels at all costs these days but remembered the pair of Manolo Blahniks I bought after watching the Sex and the City movie YEARS ago.  In the box was a typed set of instructions for what was to happen to those shoes when I died. 

I went through IVF for years before I had my daughter and in the last stages had resigned to never having a child. I remember updating our wills in those last months of IVF and leaving this note with this pair of Manolos.  A note for my friend Mel to be given these shoes after my death.  But it wasn’t the note which made me pause, it was the date on the note. The date of 10.05.17 was the day I had my very last embryo transfer.  Another transfer I thought wouldn’t work but the one which had me holding my daughter in my arms 9 months later.

I don’t think Manolo Blahnik had imaginative 6 year old girls on his ideal client vision board but seemed no better time to wear the fancy shoes with crazy socks on an ordinary Wednesday afternoon.

Watch One Day, tell your person you love them, wear the fancy shoes and buy a 5kg Wagyu brisket from the butcher because life is damn short.

Hi, I’m wedding photographer Dennis Tan.  I’ve been a pro photographer just over ten years - operating around Perth, the Swan Valley, the Southwest, interstate and overseas.

I transform kinetic moments into creative wedding imagery.
Kinetic moments are those fast-moving flashes of awesomeness that vanish in an instant. I’ve made it my mission to capture these moments, to create beautiful motion infused stills- imagery of enduring meaning and value.

And I’m a fast operator. Early in my career I was a sports photographer, capturing fast moving action really comes in handy at weddings!

My clients say I keep things light-hearted and fun. I find melting away self-consciousness with humour helps people be themselves, it’s how I create great portraits and great experiences.
Follow me and my work on FB, IG and my website:  dennistancreative.com.au

Got a question or like to make a booking? Call me, shoot me a message or email, I’m always happy to chat!

✨Struggling with reels?✨

Reels can be tricky especially if you’re not used to filming yourself on camera. There are many tips out there to have an eye catching reel but here are 5 easy tips you can try! 

1.Have the text within the blue lines. When you are typing something and move it around the page, lines should come up on the sides. Make sure to not put the text past those lines! 

2.Add transitions. When editing your reel there’s a transitions button, you can use some to make your reels look eye catching.

3.Make sure your reel is less than 15 seconds long. Instagram just pushes out shorter reels! 

4.Use hashtags in your caption below. As well as posts put those hashtags

5.Use trendy music. You can usually see if it’s trendy if there’s an arrow pointing up towards the sound.

➡️ Editing vs Retouching: What’s the Difference?

✨ Ever wonder why some photos have that extra touch of magic? Let’s talk about *editing* vs *retouching*, using a photo from my most recent wedding gallery as an example!

 First Image –> Editing:
Basic adjustments to lighting, contrast, and color correction have been made. The focus is on enhancing the natural vibe of the photo, making it more polished without altering too much. You’ll notice improved sharpness and color balance, giving the image a clean finish.

 Second Image –> Retouching:
Here’s where the magic happens! Retouching goes beyond editing by focusing on skin smoothing, removing small imperfections, refining makeup, and enhancing finer details. The result? A flawless, magazine-ready look without losing the essence of the subjects.

‼️ What does this mean to you as a future bride/groom? It’s very important that you hire a photographer to capture your special day who is proficient in ✨both✨ Lightroom (for editing) and Photoshop (for retouching)!

Capturing Love: A Beautiful Pakistani Wedding at Milan Palace, Southall
We had the honour of providing wedding photography and videography services for a delightful young Pakistani bride and groom on their special day at Milan Palace, Southall, West London. 

http://www.foreverlovewedding.com/

Pakistani weddings are known for their vibrance, cultural richness, and meaningful traditions. The main wedding ceremony, known as "Nikah," is a sacred event where the couple formally accepts one another as life partners in the presence of witnesses. It’s a beautiful, serene moment filled with prayers and blessings. Following the Nikah, the groom’s family hosted a grand "Walima" reception, a joyous celebration signifying the conclusion of the wedding festivities and the couple’s new journey together.

https://www.facebook.com/LondonandUKWeddingPhotographerandVideographer

During the couple’s shoot, they kept laughing nervously, unsure of how to pose.

Beyond capturing stunning visuals, we also offer bridal hair and makeup services to ensure that brides look and feel their best on their big day.

If you're planning your wedding and looking for experienced professionals to document your love story, we would be honoured to be part of your celebration.

✨It’s so lovely seeing new faces here, so let me take a moment for a quick reintroduction!

 So, from the beginning... I’m originally from Poland, and my journey to photography has been anything but conventional. After working in the corporate world for a short while, I realised it wasn’t for me. So, I decided to pursue something that sparked my creativity. Moving to London in 2019 (after stints in France and Scotland), photography quickly became my way of capturing the world around me, especially through the lens of love and celebration.

 While I started off experimenting with all kinds of photography—street photography in London, fashion projects, photographing concerts, art exhibitions, and real estate— it was a friend’s suggestion to try wedding photography that led me to discover my true calling.

 I approach every wedding with a quiet focus—waiting for those candid, unscripted moments that tell the story of the day. It’s all about patience and a little bit of stealth—if I’m quiet enough, people forget I’m there, and I get those natural moments.

 I’m also excited to share that my brand has recently become official—Just Stories Studio!!! With this new chapter comes refreshed energy, new vibes, and a brand-new website showcasing my best work from the past years. I’ve also created fresh guides for couples who book with me, filled with helpful tips to make their wedding day even more memorable.

✨I’d love to see you soon!

Joanne & Antonio | Boda en Londres
Equipo y settings: Canon 5D Mark III
Lens 24mm, 1/640s, f5.6, 1250 ISO
.
Trinity Buoy Wharf fue el increíble sitio elegido por esta bonita pareja para celebrar su boda. 
No es un sitio convencional, se trata de una zona industrial al este de Londres donde se encuentra el único faro de la ciudad. Un lugar muy diferente, digno de visitar, rodeado de edificios hechos con contenedores y calles ya olvidadas. 
Me gustó mucho ese ambiente caótico y busqué una composición llena de lineas diagonales que se cortan unas a otras.
Y para darle sentido y equilibrio a esta composición me bastó con buscar su mirada y esa fuerte conexión entre ellos dos. ¿Qué os parece?
.
.
.
.

✨Wednesdays Wedding Tip✨

Let’s talk flowers… 

Weddings are full of excited nerves and anticipation and while that energy is welcome… we don’t want to see it in the photos so remember that holding your flowers low will make you appear much more relaxed in the images. Plus you’ve bought a gorgeous dress which we need to see. So my tip today is to hold em LOW. Think in line with your belly button and keep those elbows loosely bent and you will exude not only elegance but confidence! 

This goes for all your bridesmaids too, keep the flowers low and in line. Your final images will look neat and clean and have a timeless look. This is mainly directed in areas such as your formal photos and walking down the isle. 

So… you’ve spent a bomb on your flowers, especially your bouquet! If you want to follow the tradition of throwing a bouquet be sure to throw a bridesmaids. That way you can have the option to preserve yours post wedding. There’s so many small businesses that offer a preservation services it seems rude not to use them! That way not only will you keep the photos as your lasting memory but the flowers will be something to keep after the big day too! 

✨Bonus Tip! ✨

If you’re emotional and know there’s a chance of some tears during your ceremony, be prepared and stuff a tissue in the back of your bouquet. So when the tears begging to flow, you got yourself covered with an emergency supply! (You’re welcome ) 

Want some more tips and tricks on how to get the most out of your wedding photography?…

See ya next Wednesday! 

Love L xxx

Do I Need a Wedding Photographer Shot List?

Brides and grooms often ask me, “Do I need a wedding photographer shot list?” It’s a great question. As a Long Island wedding photographer, I love this question because it shows that the couple want to help me help them. A wedding photography shot list lets me know which photos are important to them, and why. Knowing the why helps me see the couple as they see themselves. This knowledge provides creative inspiration throughout their wedding day.

To view more photos, please check out my Long Island wedding photography galleries and blog by clicking on my profile link.

This is Laura’s favourite photo from her wedding. Here’s how I captured it.⁠
⁠
Anyone could have taken this photo if they were in the right place at the right time. The framing would still need to be bang on, however.⁠
⁠
The question is, what led me to shoot from the top of the stairs in the first place so that I was ready before the 'moment'? ⁠
⁠
An obvious place to shoot a bride coming down the stairs is from the bottom of the stairs. It’s the safest bet for getting a photo that the bride would be happy with (and that’s what it’s all about ultimately). ⁠
⁠
However, that would have meant shooting against a mad amount of backlight that was emanating from the window at the top of the stairs⁠
⁠
This would not have been ideal because 1) it makes autofocus a nightmare and 2) dynamic range becomes an issue.⁠
⁠
But there was a third option - work with the light, not against it. ⁠
⁠
The scene was evenly illuminated from the top of the stairs and it provided a different look on an otherwise standard scene. ⁠
⁠
The moment that I was expecting (the bride leaving for the church) unexpectedly and rapidly turned into something else and shot through the moment.⁠
⁠
The final photo was cropped slightly to accentuate the father of the bride's helpless hand popping down from the top of the frame. ⁠
⁠
I'll be sharing loads more behind-the-scenes stuff on my upcoming workshop on 14 March in Nottingham (Link in Bio)⁠
⁠
See you there!⁠

caption:
“·· : the action or process of investing money for profit or material result.”

It used to bug me when I saw other photographers using the word ‘investment’ instead of ‘pricing’ on their websites. I know, I know - it’s petty but it would still get to me 

After all, an investment is something you undertake expecting a financial return (profit) in the future.

Wedding photos aren’t like that. You can’t sell them later for more than you paid, nor make any financial returns on them!

Well, photos may not be an investment in the same way you might trade stocks, purchase commodities or buy a house, but I’m starting to understand how their value goes up over time 

Not their financial value. Their *emotional* value.

Have you ever looked through old photographs in your mom’s attic with utter nostalgia? 

And felt this deep longing looking back over happy times when you realize how many people in the photographs are no longer with us?

Or just a sense that those were happy times and now everything’s changed?

The Japanese (of course) have a word for this: '  ' - A melancholic appreciation of the transiency of existence ⏳️

Well, THIS is the present moment, friends. Your wedding is that happier time that you’ll look back on in years to come 

You’ll have wistfulness, this    of how beautiful you were then, how loving your family was, how grateful you are to have had this once-in-a-lifetime event where everything is memorialized forever and everyone is together. Vital. Joyful.

I won’t start calling it anything other than ‘pricing’ on my website, but I’m starting to understand the idea of investing in photos. I’m here for it.

caption:
The journey of a wedding photographer can be challenging, especially when starting out or trying to secure those first few bookings. 

But remember, it’s completely normal. We’ve all been through this. 

Often, people only showcase their successes on social media, leaving out the struggles. 

Today, I’m breaking that pattern and sharing my own experience with you. 
A pivotal moment back in 2015 in San Francisco not only transformed my perspective as a photographer but also as a business owner. 

I could repeat this forever it’s all about the whole journey, not just the fluff! #PhotographerLife

Do you feel overwhelmed by the constant need to produce fresh and engaging social media content as a wedding photographer? 

Here’s a mini content calendar you can use to help you create and connect with your community:

MONDAY - Share a wedding industry tip. Reveal your expertise with ideas like “Top 3 poses for camera-shy couples” or “My 3 favorite wedding venues in Lake Como.”

TUESDAY - Show a day in your life. People adore behind-the-scenes content, even the “boring” parts. Give them a glimpse of your authentic daily life!

WEDNESDAY - Wedding gallery. Share a memorable wedding, detailing a specific moment or the full event from start to finish. Connect with your audience by bringing them into the heart of the wedding day experience.

THURSDAY - Post creative content that adds value in your niche. Make a reel or carousel about “3 Steps to Picking Your Destination Elopement Location” or “5 Essential Tips for 2024 Brides.”

FRIDAY - Share a positive story from your clients. If you don’t have one, share a personal achievement.

SATURDAY - Upload wedding photos, each telling a different or complementary story (details, first looks, celebrations).

SUNDAY - Step back from social media and cook homemade pizza  (or pasta )

Get to know your photographer 

Oh hey there! I’m Zephy and i’ll be your photographer this year (fingers crossed  ) so I thought I’d share some things you should know about me! ⬇️

 My name is Zephy (Zephyre is my full name!)
 I’m a mum of three and they are crazy, wild and beautiful (you can see them here @zephyrerose )
 I live in Arbroath, Angus lived here for 3.5 years now and I love it!
 I take Fine Art Weddings and Portraits which means your images look so good in print.
 I’m a 90’s kid!! I get to say that being born in the late 80’s, those were the best times! 
 I have been a wedding photographer for 8 years and honestly believe it’s the best job in the world.
 I can’t resist a sunset, soaking up those golden rays and taking a photo or two!
 I love running, it’s time for just me and I regularly attend Parkrun as I love the community.
 Colour is life! I’m super drawn to anything colourful and my photography reflects this. 
 Autumn is my favourite season. Isn’t it just the prettiest as well as being perfect for photographs?
 Loves a pizza  nothing else to say on that! 

Let’s get to know each other in the comments, come say hey! ❤️

Guaranteed to be dancing with you 

If there is one thing I can promise after my weddings in Angus this year, is that I will be there dancing with you! Still snapping away on my camera of course  

By this point on your wedding day I would have taken literally thousands of photographs already, and it’s when I finally allow myself to relax a little bit and just have some creative fun with you guys. From intimate photographs getting in on the dancing action, creative photography using flash, to fun moments just dancing with your pals! This will be the finale of our beautiful day together and I intend to go out with a bang and leave the night laughing! 

So do you fancy having a dancing photographer? Dance into my DM’s and get to know me!

Intimate Farm Wedding - Watch me at work! 

I love weddings, especially the ones where it’s at a location that is completely unique to the couple. This wedding was photographed on a dairy farm, and the whole day was filled with cows, tractors and pitchforks!

What is your unique wedding location? Let me know in the comments! ⬇️

Todays top tip is all about group photographs. 

Less is most definitely more at this point of your day. These images take up a lot of time and i work with my couples to tailor this photo list of must haves ahead of the day. 

I have a set list of images which i send over to all my couples a few months ahead of the wedding day, these being of the wedding party and immediate family only. There is around 15 groups in this list which takes around 20 -30 minutes to do. If there are any other guests that are important to the couple i will add these in. There is always time for more candid moments with guests through out the day that is more natural.

It’s good to be different 

I have always been a bit different from everyone else, including in my photography career. The industry is full of photographers so apart from having my signature fine art portfolio, I have found smart ways of attracting dream clients that I know will love my work here in Angus. 

Here are three things I do differently from other photographers in Angus Scotland ⬇️ 

1. I find a lot of clients from building genuine connections and returning clients around Arbroath and Angus. I value getting to really know people first and in turn that shows in the storytelling in my photographs, I love being able to tell people’s stories authentically! 

2. A lot of my clients find me through my personal portraits documenting my family lifestyle. When I’m not working, I’m capturing my life over at @zephyrerose photography is my whole world and I feel lucky enough to be able to do it in my spare time as well. 

3. I believe in being compatible with clients and them seeing my work as fine art to print on their walls. It’s taken a long time to get to this point in my career, having clients who understand that photographs deserve to be seen on walls, not just hidden away on phones.

If this sounds like we’re be compatible, comment ME and I’ll send you a message

caption:
Elegant Yacht Proposal in Corfu: A Moment of Pure Sophistication

Amidst the serene Ionian waters, a luxury yacht set the stage for an intimate and refined proposal in Corfu. With the sun casting a soft glow over the open deck, every detail was curated to perfection—crisp white florals, chilled champagne, and the endless blue stretching beyond.

As they sailed past Corfu’s storied coastline, he took her hand and, with effortless grace, knelt before her. The moment was pure, timeless—a quiet promise exchanged in the most exquisite of settings.

For those seeking an impeccably styled luxury proposal in Corfu, where every element speaks of elegance, we craft experiences that leave a lasting impression.

Edited by @aftershootco

✨Struggling with reels?✨

Reels can be tricky especially if you’re not used to filming yourself on camera. There are many tips out there to have an eye catching reel but here are 5 easy tips you can try! 

1.Have the text within the blue lines. When you are typing something and move it around the page, lines should come up on the sides. Make sure to not put the text past those lines! 

2.Add transitions. When editing your reel there’s a transitions button, you can use some to make your reels look eye catching.

3.Make sure your reel is less than 15 seconds long. Instagram just pushes out shorter reels! 

4.Use hashtags in your caption below. As well as posts put those hashtags

5.Use trendy music. You can usually see if it’s trendy if there’s an arrow pointing up towards the sound.

As someone who is more of an artist at heart than a businessperson (much to my chagrin at times, lol), I tend to overthink every little detail. I always want everything to be just right. Stay tuned for more details next week when I officially launch my site!

caption:
// We’re giving away a free wedding photography package! ⬇️ Keep reading to find out more ⬇️ Being in the wedding industry, it becomes obvious pretty quickly what most vendors/venues really care about. I mean, you can just say the word “wedding,” and the price quadruples ‍♀️ Yes, it’s great to make money. It’s great to hustle. It’s GREAT to grow your business.

BUT we never want the hustle to take away from our ability to bless & care for others. We want to make money (obviously), but we also want to make a lasting impact in people’s lives.

We’ve decided to start offering one free wedding each year to a couple who will really benefit from it. That could be because of extreme financial hardship, a recent tragedy, medical emergencies, etc. We truly wish we could do more than one, because we never want to see someone miss out on having amazing wedding pictures due to being in a challenging situation.

If that sounds like you, you can go to the link in our bio to fill out an application. If you know someone who could benefit from this, feel free to send this post to them so they can fill out the application as well. //

Amici Fotografi in Italia! Ad Aprile torna nostro amato @thecircleworkshop

Che cosa è? 
WORKSHOP DI FOTOGRAFIA DI MATRIMONIO in Toscana, 18-19 Aprile 2023.

Questa volta saranno con noi due fotografi importanti della scena matrimoniale Daniele Torella e Giandomenico Cosentino.

Chi sono i nostri speaker?

Artisti, fotografi di matrimonio premiati, amici, persone aperte alla condivisione per aiutare altri fotografi nella loro crescita.

Di cosa tratterà il workshop?

Parleremo di percorsi, ispirazioni, marketing, clienti, scelte artistiche, album e tanto altro. Avrai la possibilità di fotografare spalla a spalla con i maestri durante un photo shoot di coppia e fare una lettura del tuo portfolio. In più conoscerai atri fotografi, mangerai bene e passerai due giorni nel cuore della bellissima campagna Toscana.

Quando e dove?

Il workshop si svolgerà dal 18 al 19 aprile 2023 a Riparbella, Cecina, Toscana.

Come prenotare?

Segui il link del linktr.ee in bio, vai alla pagina e compila il form di prenotazione in fondo alla pagina.

Ci vediamo ad aprile!

Arthur e Lolly ✨

 
Arthur & Lolly’s love story found its perfect backdrop along the breathtaking shores of the Amalfi and Sorrento coasts. A destination wedding filled with spontaneity, emotions, and unfiltered moments, captured through the art of reportage photography. Every laugh, every tear, every embrace, just as it happened. 

•

Arthur e Lolly hanno scelto il fascino senza tempo della Costiera Sorrentina e Amalfitana per il loro giorno speciale. Un matrimonio vissuto nella spontaneità, senza pose forzate, con emozioni autentiche e istanti preziosi catturati così come sono nati. Un racconto fotografico che lascia spazio alla bellezza della realtà.

A Day of Love, Laughter & Forever 
The perfect wedding is not just about the decor or the venue, but about the love that fills the air. From the tender exchange of vows to the first dance under twinkling lights, every moment was pure magic. This couple’s love story came to life in the most breathtaking way, and we were lucky to capture it all—preserving every smile, every hug, and every unforgettable second. 

 2025 couples, it’s time to book your dream wedding photographer! Let’s make your special day as magical as this one.

So... last week didn't exactly go as planned.

My surgery was cancelled 4 hours *after* I arrived at the hospital, and we had no choice but to pack up and go home.

The only way I can describe it is that it was a roller coaster. I dropped everything to add this into my schedule with short notice, and mentally tried to prepare as much as I could. And then even more quickly, the brakes slammed and everything came to a stop. I felt so. many. feelings. So many. And now I'm just trying to pick up where I left off and make the most of it, doing things like going swimming and playing with my cats. Things that I wouldn't have been able to do for a while had my surgery actually happened.

And of course, that includes being back in the office for business as usual! 

Here's what's coming up this month:

➡️ New episodes of @keepingitcandidpodcast
➡️ The Wedding Business CEO Summit (link in bio to sign up for free!)
➡️ Details about a new template coming to the shop in March

So many new faces here from all of the couples who recently showed interest in working together so I wanted to do this little intro ✌

My name is Carlo and I am a Toronto-based wedding photographer who specializes in both film and digital photography. I approach weddings with a personal touch and focus on genuine connections and relationships with my clients. 

As someone who would be with you on one of the most important day of your lives, my priority is to create a comfortable space where you can be yourself and provide guidance/assisstance on key moments and whenever they are necessary.

A little bit about me: I worked in advertising and tech in the last 8 years - I recently quit the corporate world to pursue wedding photography as my main focus this year. You can talk to me about Vietnamese coffee and food, travel, football/basketball, music festivals and EDM for hours and I probably won’t shut up. I also train jiu-jitsu as a hobby - being on the mats serve as my mental outlet whenever I am stressed. I am also spending Q1 of this year in Asia to recharge for the rest of 2025 ✌

If you are new here, welcome and nice to meet you :)

A few dates are still open for 2025, and currently taking on 2026 wedding dates - inquire via the form on the website or message me directly.

ABOUT ME

I’m Angela, a self-taught photographer with a deep love for nature, connection, and the
light that dances through it all. I didn’t follow a traditional path—I’ve learned through
trial, error, and a lot of passion for what I do. For me, photography is about capturing the
moments that make life feel real, whether it’s the soft glow of a sunrise, the raw
connection between people, the untamed beauty of the world around us or a woman
falling in love with herself all over again. I’m a lover of all things wild and free, always
chasing light and finding beauty in the imperfections. My work is an expression of my
journey—discovering myself, embracing the chaos of life, healing and honoring the
simple yet profound moments that make us feel truly alive.

A lover of capturing love sees beauty not only in the bond between souls but in the love
within oneself. It’s about embracing the raw, the unfiltered, the untamed — freezing
moments that pulse with genuine connection and self-acceptance. Whether it’s the way
two hearts intertwine or the quiet, powerful peace found in being at home with yourself,
every frame holds the magic of love in all its forms. The wild adventures, the stolen
glances, the deep breaths in solitude — all of it speaks to the freedom that comes from
loving fully and authentically, both with others and with yourself.

Linked above is my primary account, I wanted to separate my adult work from my family work, watch this space as it grows! 

I can’t wait to connect with you and capture those real, authentic moments that make you, you. Let’s make some memories together! Click through to my website for more of my works.

~ Australia’s Top 20 Wedding Photographers - Voted & Reviewed by Real Wedding Couples ~ 
Visit @abiaweddings’ #linkinbio to access the Best Wedding Photographers as per the thousands of ratings & reviews submitted by verified married couples. Each wedding photographer has been recommended based on the quality of their work, level of service & communication, attitude of staff and overall value. 

There are literally thousands of wedding photographers to choose from, which can make for a lot of screen time when trying to find ‘the one’ for your special day.   So, here are some tips that can help with finding a wedding photographer suited to your special day: 

1. Look for technical expertise: wedding photographers must have a strong understanding of techniques, including lighting, composition, and camera settings. You can generally find this information on their website or by looking at the diverse range of indoor and outdoor photography on their social media.  
2. Creativity: they must possess a creative eye, allowing them to capture unique and memorable shots. They should be able to think outside the box and come up with creative ways to showcase the couple's personalities and the special moments of the day. 
3. Communication skills: an established wedding vendor will generally take 24 - 48 hours to respond to your queries. Ensure that communication is prompt as this will give you an indication as to how easily you can reach them closer to the wedding.  
4. Check online reviews: Look for reviews and testimonials from previous clients on reputable 3rd party platforms. This can give you an idea of their quality of work and level of service - insight from recently married couples are golden!  
Overall, a great wedding photographer should be a skilled, creative, and professional individual who is passionate about their craft and committed to providing their clients with stunning images that will be treasured for years to come.

Destination Wedding Photographer in Portugal – Capture Your Love Story in Paradise

Hi, my name is Dima Voinalovych. I’m a professional wedding photographer, passionate about capturing timeless and emotional moments in the most breathtaking locations in Portugal.

Portugal offers the perfect setting for your dream wedding – golden beaches, historic castles, and picturesque vineyards. My goal is to document every moment of your special day with authenticity and elegance while letting you fully enjoy your celebration.

Whether you’re planning an intimate elopement in Sintra, a beachside ceremony in the Algarve, or a luxurious wedding in Lisbon, I’ll ensure your love story is told in a way that reflects your emotions and connection.

Let’s make your destination wedding unforgettable! I’d love to hear about your plans and create stunning memories that will last a lifetime.

 Contact me today to discuss your vision!

Vocês precisam ler esta historia e ver as imagens até o final. Nessa magnifica aventura, o destino foi a ilha da Madeira. Lugar rodeado pela natureza e uma imensa beleza. Partimos para uma das pontas da ilha e durante o caminho tive um insight. Minha sogra nos acompanhava e a desafiei a fazer um ensaio meu e da Mel. De facto o resultado da beleza de uma imagem está na autenticidade do instante. Ela nunca havia fotografado com uma maquina profissional. O que eu disse a ela para alem de uns toques de onde se posicionar foi: Dispara, dispara! hahaha… Que incrível!

এই কথাটি তোমাদের কাছে কতটা গ্রহণযোগ্য বলতে পারবোনা, তবে আমার মনে হয় ছোটো ছোটো স্বপ্ন দিয়ে কিভাবে একটা বাস্তব গড়ে তোলা যায় তা তোমাদের ওই স্বপ্নের আস্তানার প্রতিটি কোণে কোণে বর্তমান। 
বলে নাকি 'Love is Freedom', আর সংসার মানে কলরব - এইসবের মাঝে তোমাদের প্রেম একটা নদীর মতো যে নিজের দিশায় পথ বানিয়ে নেয়! তাই আশা রাখি এভাবেই তোমরা একে অপরের শক্তি হয়ে সাহস যুগিয়ে চলো, জীবনের শেষ অবধি। 

তাই আমাদের তরফ থেকে কিছু মুহুর্ত উপহার তোমাদের জন্য!

~ Australia’s Top 20 Wedding Photographers - Voted & Reviewed by Real Wedding Couples ~ 
Visit @abiaweddings’ #linkinbio to access the Best Wedding Photographers as per the thousands of ratings & reviews submitted by verified married couples. Each wedding photographer has been recommended based on the quality of their work, level of service & communication, attitude of staff and overall value. 

There are literally thousands of wedding photographers to choose from, which can make for a lot of screen time when trying to find ‘the one’ for your special day.   So, here are some tips that can help with finding a wedding photographer suited to your special day: 

1. Look for technical expertise: wedding photographers must have a strong understanding of techniques, including lighting, composition, and camera settings. You can generally find this information on their website or by looking at the diverse range of indoor and outdoor photography on their social media.  
2. Creativity: they must possess a creative eye, allowing them to capture unique and memorable shots. They should be able to think outside the box and come up with creative ways to showcase the couple's personalities and the special moments of the day. 
3. Communication skills: an established wedding vendor will generally take 24 - 48 hours to respond to your queries. Ensure that communication is prompt as this will give you an indication as to how easily you can reach them closer to the wedding.  
4. Check online reviews: Look for reviews and testimonials from previous clients on reputable 3rd party platforms. This can give you an idea of their quality of work and level of service - insight from recently married couples are golden!  
Overall, a great wedding photographer should be a skilled, creative, and professional individual who is passionate about their craft and committed to providing their clients with stunning images that will be treasured for years to come.

My love affair with my camera began when I had my first baby 30 years ago and a desire to take photos of her and over time developed into an obsession with how to operate this baffling piece of equipment and capture something really good (the early photos were really bad)

My darling niece Nell asked me to photograph her wedding in 2014 and that is when I realized what all the years of practising had been for! I adore weddings for the challenge and incredible opportunities to push the boundaries of creativity and learning. And I love falling in love with my couples, it happens every time. That I get to deliver to them images that they love is the biggest rush of endorphins ever!

There’s something about film that digital just can’t replicate. The grain, the texture, the way light lingers on every frame—it’s storytelling in its purest form.

Film slows everything down. It captures the in-between moments, the fleeting glances, the quiet beauty of your love exactly as it is—raw, imperfect, and deeply real. These aren’t just photos; they’re memories, sealed in time, with every frame holding the depth of the moment it was taken.

Julie & Fran – A Beautifully Personal Day at Poulton Civic Centre

Julie and Fran tied the knot at the Civic Centre in Poulton, choosing my Essentials Package, which covers up to four hours—perfect for capturing their ceremony, family portraits, and candid moments with guests.

What made their day extra special was the handmade decorations, crafted by the couple themselves. Every detail reflected their love and personality, with a strong focus on family being at the heart of their celebration.

They were also game for a laugh and didn’t take themselves too seriously, which made for some brilliant, fun moments throughout the day! It was an absolute joy to document such an intimate and meaningful celebration.

Congratulations, Julie & Fran!

✅ Need just a few hours for an intimate elopement? No problem.

3 months without my camera…to be honest it feels very good I needed a break! Don’t get me wrong I love my camera, I love taking photos, I love the happy smiles of my clients and the tears when they get their beautiful memories  But after a wedding season like last year (over 100 photoshoots, including 30 weddings) I definitely needed it!! It‘s important to take breaks & calm down after such a busy time. Because I’m not a robot and I’m not producing the same photos for every client. I put so much thought & time & heart in every little & big shooting. That takes a lot of energy, which needs to be reloaded during the winter time. Some of you know that I spend half of the year in Germany (Hamburg) and the other half in Ireland (Sligo) where my boyfriend lives. At the moment I’m in Ireland and take my time to relax and refill my energy
Anyway, I can't wait to get back to shooting weddings and firing up my camera. 2022 is going to be wild!!!

–

Clare

✨ When you finally find a wedding photographer who gets you… and your good side. 

At McGlade Photography & Film, we don’t just capture moments—we steal them (legally, of course). From the teary-eyed vows to that one uncle breaking it down on the dance floor like it’s 1999, we’re there for it all. 

But here’s the kicker:
 Photography & Videography? We’ve got BOTH, so you won’t have to juggle vendors like your nan juggling plates at the buffet.
⏳ Speedy delivery? Yep—your memories will arrive faster than you can say, “Where’s my wedding video?”
️ Cinematic & modern? Think less awkward posing, more you being you (but with better lighting).

So, whether you’re planning an intimate ceremony or a full-on festival of love, we’re here to make sure your story looks as epic as it feels. ❤️
